        jTextArea1.setText("Poker Instructions\nTo change the difficulty of the AI player, click the drop down box and select between easy, medium, or hard. Easy will be the\ndefault selection if nothing else is picked.\n\nTo begin playing, click the start button.\n\nYou will then be asked to enter a starting wager.\n\nOnce entered, you and the AI player will be both dealt 3 cards, and\nadditional cards will be dealt in the center of the screen as the center hand, with 2 cards faced up and the rest faced down.\nThe center hand acts as cards that both players have in their hand.\n\n\nFour options will be availbe to you to select from by clicking on their respective button, each of which are explined below.\n\nCall: Pressing the Call button keeps your wager the same or raises your wager to whatever the AI player raised their wager\nif they picked raise.\n\nRaise: Raises your amount wagered by the amount specified in the text below the Raise button.\n\nHold: Passes your turn to the AI player's. After the AI player goes, it will be your turn again, and you cannot pick the Hold\noption for the rest of the current betting round.\n\nFold: Foldng will have you stop betting ending the current game, and give the AI player your current wager, with them as the\nwinner.\n\nOnce you and the AI player have both picked an option and have matched wagers, the current betting round will end and one of\nthe three face down cards will be faced up. Then a new betting round will begin. This cycle continues until all cards in the\ncenter hand are faced up.\n\nBecause of this, the showdown round will now begin, where both players will reveal their hands to each other, and the player\nwith the highest valued hand will be declared the winner and will keep their wager and gain the opposing player's waged money.\n\nTwo options will then be presented to you, Rematch and Quit.\nClicking Rematch will allow you to challenge the AI player to another game of poker with the money earned from the previous game \nadded.\nClicking Quit will exit the program.\n\n");
        jScrollPane1.setViewportView(jTextArea1);

